### THEORIST Round 1

We proved a useful geometric lemma: whenever three distinct points of a support set in C_p^3 lie on an affine line, those three points already force a short zero-sum of length ≤ p, so any extremal support for η(C_7^3) cannot contain a collinear triple and therefore must be an affine cap. This is a concrete, machine-usable pruning: the naive universe of (342 choose 8) ≈ 7×10^13 8-sets collapses to the much smaller family of 8-caps in AG(3,7) (classically about 3.3×10^8), a six-order-of-magnitude reduction that makes a systematic computer search feasible; next I will implement a backtracking enumerator for 8-caps up to GL(3,7) symmetry, filter antipodal/degenerate cases, and run the 343-bit bitset DP to check uniform multiplicity 6 (stopping immediately if any extremal support is found), after which we'll try mixed multiplicities, 7/9-point supports, and DFS extensions from known length-42 sequences to hunt for the longest zero-sum-free sequences and for the universal threshold. Vibe check: (green) = real progress.

